      "main_html": "<article class=\"post-605 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-r-bloggers tag-colors tag-function tag-plot tag-r-help tag-reference\">\n<header class=\"post-header\">\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\">Tips from the R-help list : shadow text in a plot and bumps charts</h1>\n<p class=\"meta post-meta\">Posted on <span class=\"updated\">April 28, 2009</span>  by <span class=\"vcard author\"><a class=\"fn\" href=\"https://www.r-bloggers.com/author/paolo/\">Paolo</a></span>  in <a href=\"https://www.r-bloggers.com/category/r-bloggers/\" rel=\"category tag\">R bloggers</a> | 0 Comments</p>\n</header>\n<div class=\"entry clearfix\">\n<p class=\"syndicated-attribution\"><!-- \r\n<div style=\"min-height: 30px;\">\r\n[social4i size=\"small\" align=\"align-left\"]\r\n</div>\r\n-->\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid; background: none repeat scroll 0 0 #EDEDED; margin: 1px; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n[This article was first published on  <strong><a href=\"https://feedproxy.google.com/~r/OneRTipADay/~3/GeOpDznpal0/tips-from-r-help-list-shadow-text-in.html\"> One R Tip A Day</a></strong>, and kindly contributed to <a href=\"https://www.r-bloggers.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">R-bloggers</a>].  (You can report issue about the content on this page <a href=\"https://www.r-bloggers.com/contact-us/\">here</a>)\r\n<hr/>Want to share your content on R-bloggers?<a href=\"https://www.r-bloggers.com/add-your-blog/\" rel=\"nofollow\"> click here</a> if you have a blog, or <a href=\"http://r-posts.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"> here</a> if you don't.\r\n</div></p>\n\n<!-- Share buttons by mashshare.net - Version: 3.8.0-->Stumbling across the R-help mailing-list I found, as often happens,  two threads in the spirit of this blog (of course, since they come from the list, the quality is higher): <a href=\"http://article.gmane.org/gmane.comp.lang.r.general/147787\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> you can find a function allowing  a shadow outline style for a text in a plot. From <a href=\"http://www.nabble.com/Bumps-chart-in-R-td23247632.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> you can follow an interesting thread depicting how to produce <a href=\"http://junkcharts.typepad.com/junk_charts/bumps_chart/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bumps charts</a> in R.<div class=\"blogger-post-footer\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"jetpack-lazy-image\" data-lazy-src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7556813435224291579-5306496788158466696?l=onertipaday.blogspot.com&amp;is-pending-load=1\" height=\"1\" src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7556813435224291579-5306496788158466696?l=onertipaday.blogspot.com\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"1\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" height=\"1\" src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7556813435224291579-5306496788158466696?l=onertipaday.blogspot.com\" width=\"1\"/></noscript></div><img class=\"jetpack-lazy-image\" data-lazy-src=\"https://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OneRTipADay/~4/GeOpDznpal0?is-pending-load=1\" height=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OneRTipADay/~4/GeOpDznpal0\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"1\"/><noscript><img height=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OneRTipADay/~4/GeOpDznpal0\" width=\"1\"/></noscript>\n\n<div class=\"jp-relatedposts\" id=\"jp-relatedposts\">\n<h3 class=\"jp-relatedposts-headline\"><em>Related</em></h3>\n</div>\n<!-- Share buttons by mashshare.net - Version: 3.8.0-->\n<p class=\"syndicated-attribution\"><div style=\"border: 1px solid; background: none repeat scroll 0 0 #EDEDED; margin: 1px; font-size: 13px;\">\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">To <strong>leave a comment</strong> for the author, please follow the link and comment on their blog: <strong><a href=\"https://feedproxy.google.com/~r/OneRTipADay/~3/GeOpDznpal0/tips-from-r-help-list